1
00:00:07,008 --> 00:00:10,444
(Aiko) Even before you got married, you only had eyes for her.

2
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:12,446
Because I know everything.

3
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:15,950
(Seiichi) I had been dating Mr. Ando since before we got married.

4
00:00:16,017 --> 00:00:18,452
(Okada) Did you marry Aiko even though there was no love from the beginning?

5
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:19,954
(Seiichi) That's...

6
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,956
(Aiko) You're a liar!

7
00:00:22,023 --> 00:00:24,959
⟨My husband married me for one reason⟩

8
00:00:25,026 --> 00:00:28,029
⟨It was just camouflage⟩

9
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:33,534
(Aiko) Seiichi-san.

10
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,486
(Aiko) I love you.

11
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:58,492
⟨This is about me and my husband who loved each other so much that I wanted to kill them →

12
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:01,495
It is a story of rebirth⟩

13
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:12,506
♪～

14
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:17,945
(sound of door closing)

15
00:01:18,012 --> 00:01:20,014
(Okada) Aiko-san?

16
00:01:23,517 --> 00:01:25,453
(Aiko) Huh…｡

17
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:27,955
(Okada) Aiko! Aiko-san!

18
00:01:28,022 --> 00:01:30,458
Please be strong, Aiko-san!

19
00:01:30,524 --> 00:01:33,461
Excuse me, an ambulance please. (Salesperson) Understood.

20
00:01:33,527 --> 00:01:35,529
(Okada) Aiko! (Ambulance siren)

21
00:01:48,542 --> 00:01:51,979
(Yuki) Aiko-san?

22
00:01:52,046 --> 00:01:53,981
(Aiko) Mr. Yuki...

23
00:01:54,048 --> 00:01:55,983
(Okada) Ha, good.

24
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:57,985
(Yuki) This is a hospital.

25
00:01:58,052 --> 00:02:00,488
Aiko collapsed after the discussion →

26
00:02:00,554 --> 00:02:02,990
I received a call from Mr. Okada.

27
00:02:04,492 --> 00:02:06,427
(Aiko) Ha, I…｡

28
00:02:06,494 --> 00:02:07,928
(Okada) Please rest assured.

29
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:10,998
No X-rays or medications were given.

30
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,504
>> Why didn't you tell me?

31
00:02:18,506 --> 00:02:22,009
You're pregnant, right?

32
00:02:27,014 --> 00:02:31,519
(Doctor) [Congratulations, you are now in your 7th week of pregnancy]

33
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:36,957
[This is still very small]

34
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:42,463
[I think the due date will be clearer at the next checkup.]

35
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:44,965
[Just to be sure →

36
00:02:45,032 --> 00:02:48,469
Do you wish to continue your pregnancy? ] (Aiko) [Huh? ]

37
00:02:48,536 --> 00:02:51,972
>> [Ah, this is what I'm asking you all]

38
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:54,975
[Our hospital only accepts people who wish to give birth →

39
00:02:55,042 --> 00:02:56,977
Because it is not accepted]

40
00:02:57,044 --> 00:02:59,046
(Aiko) [Ah...]

41
00:03:06,487 --> 00:03:08,923
(Reception) [Mr. Sasashima]

42
00:03:08,989 --> 00:03:10,424
(Aiko) [Yes]

43
00:03:10,491 --> 00:03:12,927
>> [If things go well at your next visit →

44
00:03:12,993 --> 00:03:15,930
Please go to the government office and get a maternal and child health handbook.]

45
00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:17,431
(Aiko) [Yes]

46
00:03:17,498 --> 00:03:21,001
>> [Please take care of yourself] (Aiko) [Thank you]

47
00:03:23,003 --> 00:03:24,939
(Aiko's voice) I found out I was pregnant →

48
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:27,942
This was after I found out about Ando-san's abortion.

49
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:31,512
(Okada) You haven't talked to Seiichi.

50
00:03:33,514 --> 00:03:35,950
>> Do something with your precious body.

51
00:03:36,016 --> 00:03:37,952
(Aiko) I'm sorry.

52
00:03:38,018 --> 00:03:41,455
But I→

53
00:03:41,522 --> 00:03:44,959
I really wanted to give birth.

54
00:03:45,025 --> 00:03:46,961
(Okada) I understand how you feel.

55
00:03:47,027 --> 00:03:49,463
But I'll calm down after I get back in shape...

56
00:03:49,530 --> 00:03:51,532
(Aiko) I'm calm.

57
00:03:53,534 --> 00:03:55,469
(Okada) I don't think so.

58
00:03:55,536 --> 00:03:58,973
What Seiichi did to you is outrageous.

59
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:03,477
(Aiko) But it has nothing to do with children.

60
00:04:04,979 --> 00:04:10,918
This child came to me.

61
00:04:10,985 --> 00:04:14,421
I think it's a miraculous connection.

62
00:04:14,488 --> 00:04:18,492
That's why I want to cherish that.

63
00:04:19,994 --> 00:04:23,931
Child support and alimony from husband →

64
00:04:23,998 --> 00:04:26,500
I don't want to receive even a single yen.

65
00:04:28,002 --> 00:04:30,437
please.

66
00:04:30,504 --> 00:04:33,440
Until the divorce is finalized...→

67
00:04:33,507 --> 00:04:37,444
No, even after the divorce is finalized →

68
00:04:37,511 --> 00:04:42,516
I absolutely don't want my husband to know about our child.

69
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:50,457
I gave birth to this child alone →

70
00:04:50,524 --> 00:04:53,027
I will grow it alone.

71
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:01,969
>>You must have been worried.

72
00:05:02,036 --> 00:05:05,406
But you're not alone.

73
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:08,475
You've been working hard.

74
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,483
(Okada) I will inform the teacher that I have woken up.

75
00:05:18,986 --> 00:05:22,923
(Sound of door opening and closing)

76
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:25,926
Although I say harsh things with my mouth →

77
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:28,996
Professor Okada is also worried.

78
00:05:30,998 --> 00:05:33,000
(Aiko) I understand.

79
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:39,940
(Seiichi) Aiko! Ah...

80
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:44,945
>> Sorry for the sudden change. My name is Yuki and I am a lawyer.

81
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:46,447
(Seiichi) Hello...

82
00:05:46,513 --> 00:05:48,949
(Aiko) What is your job? what happened?

83
00:05:49,016 --> 00:05:52,453
(Seiichi) Where have you been?

84
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:56,957
>> Aiko-san, she felt a little unwell after the discussion yesterday →

85
00:05:57,024 --> 00:06:00,961
I was resting overnight at the hospital. (Seiichi) Eh, hospital?

86
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:04,398
(Aiko) It's just anemia, so it's not a big deal.

87
00:06:04,465 --> 00:06:07,401
>> I'm sorry, but →

88
00:06:07,468 --> 00:06:12,973
Mr. Sasashima, please never raise your hand against Aiko again.

89
00:06:14,475 --> 00:06:16,410
(Seiichi) Sorry...

90
00:06:16,477 --> 00:06:20,481
>> Rest in peace, Aiko. (Aiko) Yes, thank you very much.

91
00:06:22,983 --> 00:06:25,919
What about breakfast? (Seiichi) I haven't eaten it though...

92
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:29,923
(Aiko) Well, I'll get you something simple right away.

93
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,426
(Seiichi) No, it's fine, don't push yourself too hard.

94
00:06:32,493 --> 00:06:35,929
(Aiko) I'm still your wife, right?

95
00:06:35,996 --> 00:06:37,931
(Seiichi) Yes, but.

96
00:06:37,998 --> 00:06:40,934
(Aiko) Then let's make something.

97
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:46,507
Let me do my job as a wife until the end.

98
00:06:50,511 --> 00:06:51,945
(Seiichi) Work...

99
00:06:52,012 --> 00:06:59,453
📱(vibration sound)

100
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,955
(Seiichi) Ah, wait a minute... 📱(Vibration sound)

101
00:07:02,022 --> 00:07:03,891
📱(vibration sound)

102
00:07:03,957 --> 00:07:06,393
(Sound of door opening and closing)

103
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,396
(Seiichi) Hello. 📱(Ayaka) What's wrong? You're late.

104
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:11,899
(Seiichi) No, Aiko is not feeling well.

105
00:07:11,965 --> 00:07:14,902
📱 It doesn't matter anymore!

106
00:07:14,968 --> 00:07:17,404
(Seiichi) I have to make sure I don't lose my temper any further.

107
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:21,408
📱 Haha~ The reason you don't do well is because of the money.

108
00:07:21,475 --> 00:07:24,411
📱 I absolutely hate 10 million.

109
00:07:24,478 --> 00:07:26,413
(Seiichi) I understand.

110
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,415
Well then.

111
00:07:28,482 --> 00:07:40,928
♪～

112
00:07:40,994 --> 00:07:42,996
(Aiko) Sit down.

113
00:07:52,506 --> 00:07:55,008
(Seiichi) Are you still sick?

114
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:04,384
(Aiko) Until the divorce is finalized →

115
00:08:04,451 --> 00:08:08,455
I will continue to do the housework as usual.

116
00:08:09,957 --> 00:08:14,962
This is my last intention as a wife.

117
00:08:16,463 --> 00:08:18,966
(Seiichi) As a job?

118
00:08:20,467 --> 00:08:25,973
(Aiko) Yes, my job as a wife.

119
00:08:30,477 --> 00:08:35,415
(Aiko) I didn't think so from the beginning →

120
00:08:35,482 --> 00:08:39,419
If you don't make that distinction →

121
00:08:39,486 --> 00:08:42,489
I felt like my heart would break.

122
00:08:49,496 --> 00:08:52,933
(Aiko) You didn't know, right?

123
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:59,940
My married life with you→

124
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:03,877
I've been lonely forever →

125
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:06,446
It was always painful.

126
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,454
(Aiko) I'll make some tea.

127
00:09:16,456 --> 00:09:19,393
(Seiichi) I am aware that I did something terrible.

128
00:09:19,459 --> 00:09:21,461
sorry.

129
00:09:24,965 --> 00:09:28,402
(Seiichi) Yesterday, I met that lawyer →

130
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:33,907
I was asked if I got married even though I didn't have love →

131
00:09:33,974 --> 00:09:36,476
I flinched for a moment.

132
00:09:39,479 --> 00:09:41,982
(Seiichi) Pathetic...

133
00:09:45,986 --> 00:09:48,488
(Seiichi) Aiko You see...｡ 📱(Vibration sound)

134
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,003
(Seiichi) Ah, sorry...｡

135
00:10:04,504 --> 00:10:06,940
I have to go now.

136
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:09,009
(Aiko) Seiichi-san.

137
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:15,015
I have one request.

138
00:10:19,519 --> 00:10:21,521
(Seiichi) What?

139
00:10:24,024 --> 00:10:27,961
(Aiko) On the last day →

140
00:10:28,028 --> 00:10:31,031
Would you like to have dinner with me?

141
00:10:35,535 --> 00:10:38,038
(Aiko) My punishment.

142
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:45,545
(Seiichi) I understand.

143
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:50,050
(Aiko) Thank you.

144
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:29,022
(Aiko) 《I was really happy when I got married》

145
00:11:29,089 --> 00:11:33,026
(Voice of MC) The bride and groom are entering.

146
00:11:33,093 --> 00:11:39,966
(applause)

147
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,968
\Congratulations! /

148
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:45,472
(Sawako) Aiko~ Cute!

149
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:48,475
To Sawako Shigemoto, a friend of the bride Aiko →

150
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:51,545
I would like to ask you to give a congratulatory speech.

151
00:11:53,046 --> 00:11:57,984
I'm Sawako Shigemoto, a friend of Aiko's since high school.

152
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,487
Aiko since her school days →

153
00:12:00,554 --> 00:12:03,490
Taking care of my grandmother who lives with me →

154
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:07,994
He is a kind person who always thinks about the people around him more than himself →

155
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:10,997
He is a friend I truly respect.

156
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:16,002
What if my friend got married to such a cool and elite husband?

157
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:19,506
To be honest, I'm a little jealous →

158
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:25,011
But since she is Aiko, I am filled with congratulations from the bottom of my heart.

159
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,514
Aiko surely→

160
00:12:27,581 --> 00:12:31,518
Grandma in heaven is happy too.

161
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:36,456
From now on, put yourself first and be happy.

162
00:12:36,523 --> 00:12:39,960
Congratulations! (applause)

163
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:43,463
(Aiko) 《I don't have time to play because I'm caring for my grandmother and helping around the house→

164
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,966
For me, who has zero love experience →

165
00:12:46,032 --> 00:12:50,470
The first boyfriend I met was Seiichi.

166
00:12:50,537 --> 00:12:54,975
(Seiichi) Everyone, please come today for the two of us →

167
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,977
thank you.

168
00:12:57,043 --> 00:13:02,983
Although we are immature, from now on, Aiko and I will be a couple →

169
00:13:03,049 --> 00:13:06,987
We will overcome any difficulties.

170
00:13:07,053 --> 00:13:09,990
From now on, for the sake of my family →

171
00:13:10,056 --> 00:13:13,994
I intend to work even harder.

172
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:17,497
>>What is your vow of love? (laughs)

173
00:13:17,564 --> 00:13:25,505
Oath! Oath! Oath...! (claps)

174
00:13:25,572 --> 00:13:28,508
(Seiichi) Aiko...

175
00:13:28,575 --> 00:13:31,511
I love you and I will make you happy!

176
00:13:31,578 --> 00:13:34,447
(Aiko) Hehehe…｡ >> ＼Huh~! /

177
00:13:34,514 --> 00:13:40,954
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss...! (claps)

178
00:13:41,021 --> 00:13:44,457
(Aiko) 《Married with my first boyfriend》

179
00:13:44,524 --> 00:13:49,029
《It was like a fairy tale happiness》

180
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:52,465
>> ＼Fu~! /

181
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:58,038
(Aiko) 《But one year after the peak of such happiness》

182
00:13:59,539 --> 00:14:03,476
《I was thrown into hell》

183
00:14:03,543 --> 00:14:07,480
Where was the tree?

184
00:14:07,547 --> 00:14:09,983
Hmm?

185
00:14:10,050 --> 00:14:14,054
Hmm, that side?

186
00:14:15,555 --> 00:14:17,557
Yeah?

187
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,062
a….

188
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:30,570
(Aiko) I don't need something this expensive.

189
00:14:32,072 --> 00:14:41,948
♪～

190
00:14:42,015 --> 00:14:46,019
(Aiko) Okay... not yet?

191
00:14:53,026 --> 00:14:54,961
📱(vibration sound)

192
00:14:55,028 --> 00:15:10,477
♪～

193
00:15:10,543 --> 00:15:13,546
(The sound of the front door opening and closing)

194
00:15:15,548 --> 00:15:18,485
(Aiko) Ah... thank you for your hard work.

195
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:23,056
(Seiichi) I said you could sleep. (Aiko) Oh... I'm sorry.

196
00:15:26,059 --> 00:15:27,994
(Seiichi) No, I'm sorry, it's Eve.

197
00:15:28,061 --> 00:15:31,498
(Aiko) No, I have to work, so I can't help it.

198
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:35,936
(Seiichi) I'll eat the food tomorrow. I'm sleepy. (Aiko) Yeah, rest.

199
00:15:36,002 --> 00:15:38,438
(Seiichi) Ah, this is Happy Merry Christmas.

200
00:15:38,505 --> 00:15:40,940
(Aiko) Well, that's fine...｡

201
00:15:41,007 --> 00:15:44,511
(Seiichi) I heard from someone at work that this restaurant is popular.

202
00:15:51,017 --> 00:15:53,453
(Aiko) Thank you. (Seiichi) Yes.

203
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:56,456
Well, I'm tired, so I'll take a rest first.

204
00:15:56,523 --> 00:15:58,525
(Aiko) Good night.

205
00:16:00,527 --> 00:16:05,031
(Sound of door opening and closing)

206
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:28,421
♪～

207
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:30,423
📱(Transmission sound)

208
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:32,425
\Welcome/ \Welcome~/

209
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:34,427
(Aiko) Rena!

210
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:37,430
(Rena) Aiko~ It’s been a while! (Aiko) It’s been a while~｡

211
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:39,933
Hey, I'm sorry for contacting you all of a sudden. >> Hmm, I'm glad.

212
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,502
Isn't it since the wedding? (Aiko) That's right.

213
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:48,942
>> I'm sad that Aiko left the company, and to be honest, work is hard.

214
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:50,443
(Aiko) Huh?

215
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:53,880
>> Aiko did all the invisible chores →

216
00:16:53,947 --> 00:16:57,884
All the section managers were once again grateful to Aiko.

217
00:16:57,951 --> 00:17:00,887
Things went smoothly because Aiko was there→

218
00:17:00,954 --> 00:17:04,391
There's so much going on, I really want you to come back.

219
00:17:04,457 --> 00:17:07,894
(Aiko) Haha... Something makes me happy.

220
00:17:07,961 --> 00:17:11,398
>> However, Aiko would have been able to balance both →

221
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:13,900
Why did you quit your job? (Aiko) Hmm…｡

222
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:17,904
Seiichi's wish was for him to join the family.

223
00:17:17,971 --> 00:17:21,408
>> Hmm, that's rare these days.

224
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:23,410
Well, my company→

225
00:17:23,476 --> 00:17:27,914
All of my bosses have old ways of thinking, so I wonder if they've been influenced by this.

226
00:17:27,981 --> 00:17:31,918
Ah, do you mean that you simply want to have Aiko all to yourself?

227
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:33,920
(Aiko) No, it's not like that...

228
00:17:33,987 --> 00:17:36,923
>> It's okay, they're so in love, I'm jealous.

229
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:39,426
You had fun last night anyway, right?

230
00:17:39,492 --> 00:17:43,430
(Aiko) It's really different because I'm busy with work every day.

231
00:17:43,496 --> 00:17:47,434
>> Well, Mr. Sasashima, even in the business department, you are an elite person.

232
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,437
But see, Wednesday and Friday are no overtime days →

233
00:17:50,503 --> 00:17:52,439
Aren't you coming back early today?

234
00:17:52,505 --> 00:17:53,873
(Aiko) Huh?

235
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:55,875
>> Huh? It's Friday today.

236
00:17:55,942 --> 00:17:57,877
The company is also strict →

237
00:17:57,944 --> 00:18:01,448
If you stay for even 30 minutes, you'll get angry.

238
00:18:03,450 --> 00:18:06,453
(Aiko) Ah, I see.

239
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:09,889
(gurgling…)

240
00:18:09,956 --> 00:18:11,891
(Aiko) 《Painful...》

241
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:14,961
(gurgle gurgle…)

242
00:18:18,965 --> 00:18:22,902
(Aiko) 《Wednesday and Friday are always late》

243
00:18:22,969 --> 00:18:25,405
>> [Wednesday and Friday are no overtime days →

244
00:18:25,472 --> 00:18:27,907
Aren't you coming home early today? ]

245
00:18:27,974 --> 00:18:30,477
📱(vibration sound)

246
00:18:31,978 --> 00:18:33,980
(Aiko) Huh…｡

247
00:18:38,985 --> 00:18:44,924
(Aiko) Ha ha ha ha...｡

248
00:18:44,991 --> 00:19:00,373
♪～

249
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,375
(Aiko) Password...｡

250
00:19:02,442 --> 00:19:20,894
♪～

251
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,897
(Aiko) Ah... there it was.

252
00:19:23,963 --> 00:19:27,901
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

253
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:29,903
(Aiko) Opened.

254
00:19:29,969 --> 00:19:33,473
《There should be a location search app》

255
00:19:36,476 --> 00:19:38,478
(Aiko) There it was.

256
00:19:39,479 --> 00:19:41,414
(click sound)

257
00:19:41,481 --> 00:19:44,984
(Aiko) A restaurant? I guess it's entertainment.

258
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:48,488
yeah?

259
00:19:49,989 --> 00:19:51,991
Huh?

260
00:19:54,427 --> 00:19:55,862
(click sound)

261
00:19:55,929 --> 00:19:57,931
(Aiko) An apartment?

262
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:02,869
Ha ha ha ha...

263
00:20:02,936 --> 00:20:05,371
(gurgle gurgle…)

264
00:20:05,438 --> 00:20:08,441
(Aiko) 《I can't breathe》

265
00:20:10,944 --> 00:20:15,448
Moon pair apartment? Ha, somewhere...

266
00:20:19,452 --> 00:20:21,454
(click sound)

267
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:28,962
(Aiko) Moon Pair Mansion Moon Pair Mansion…｡

268
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:35,468
(Aiko) There it was.

269
00:20:42,475 --> 00:20:44,978
(Aiko) Ayaka Ando…｡

270
00:20:46,479 --> 00:20:53,853
>> [Applause]

271
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:58,358
(Aiko) Huh... That's a lie...

272
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:02,362
(Sound of pouring into glass) (Ayaka's voice) It's especially delicious today.

273
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:04,364
(Seiichi) Yeah?

274
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:07,367
(Ayaka) Because I have Eve and Christmas all to myself.

275
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:09,869
(Seiichi) Ah...

276
00:21:09,936 --> 00:21:14,374
>> Hey, was it okay for Eve to come home in the morning?

277
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,876
(Seiichi) What do you mean by holding me back?

278
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:18,878
>> Hehe…｡

279
00:21:18,945 --> 00:21:22,882
(Seiichi) But it's okay because I'm trusted.

280
00:21:22,949 --> 00:21:25,385
>> Hey.

281
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:29,889
That kid doesn't know how to doubt people →

282
00:21:29,956 --> 00:21:32,892
You're insensitive.

283
00:21:32,959 --> 00:21:35,895
He's such a bad man.

284
00:21:35,962 --> 00:21:37,897
(Seiichi) Because I thought it was bad→

285
00:21:37,964 --> 00:21:40,900
I ate homemade chicken this morning.

286
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:46,973
>> Handmade? Hehe... I'm jealous that you have free time.

287
00:21:48,975 --> 00:21:51,911
If I have time, I'll do it for Seiichi →

288
00:21:51,978 --> 00:21:55,848
I wish I could do more things for you.

289
00:21:55,915 --> 00:22:00,853
(Seiichi) He was also happy about the cookie tin that Ayaka told him about.

290
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,855
>> Stupid person.

291
00:22:02,922 --> 00:22:06,426
As expected of the person I chose to marry.

292
00:22:08,928 --> 00:22:11,431
(Seiichi) Haha. >> Hey...

293
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:15,935
Thank you for this.

294
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:20,873
(Seiichi) It suits you.

295
00:22:20,940 --> 00:22:22,375
>> Hehe…｡

296
00:22:22,442 --> 00:22:36,389
♪～

297
00:22:36,456 --> 00:22:40,393
Hey... turn off the light.

298
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:49,402
♪～

299
00:22:49,469 --> 00:22:53,339
(Aiko) ⟨This is how I was thrown into hell⟩

300
00:22:53,406 --> 00:22:55,341
⟨But→

301
00:22:55,408 --> 00:23:01,914
The real hell was still waiting for me ahead of me⟩
